11 Section 2. KRS 258.015 is amended to read as follows:
12 (1) Every owner shall have his or her dog, cat, or ferret initially vaccinated against
13 rabies by the age of four (4) months and revaccinated at the expiration of the
14 immunization period as certified by a Kentucky-licensed[the] veterinarian. The
15 veterinarian, or a Kentucky-licensed veterinary technician in accordance to KRS
16 321.190, who vaccinates a dog, cat, or ferret shall issue to the owner a vaccination
17 certificate signed by the veterinarian on a form approved by the Cabinet for Health
18 and Family Services. The vaccination certificate shall be prepared and issued in
19 duplicate, one (1) copy to be retained by the issuing veterinarian and one (1) copy
20 to be given to the owner of the dog, cat, or ferret vaccinated. Each certificate shall
21 bear the name and address of the veterinarian who issued it. The veterinarian shall
22 also furnish each dog owner with a rabies tag bearing a serial number
23 corresponding to the vaccination certificate with the year of immunization. The tag
24 shall be affixed to a collar or harness furnished by the owner and shall be worn by
25 the dog for which the tag was issued. No one except the owner or his or her duly
26 authorized agent shall remove the tag.
27 (2) Every qualified person who vaccinates his or her own dog shall comply with the
